Decision Making and Planning

  Managers make decisions, and therefore need information.
Some common decisions we will study are: 
  suppose your company makes medical probes. 
  In July, you receive a call from a company that is not a regular 
customer. 
  They would like to purchase 5000 probes this month only, and
the price they offer is below your production cost. 
  Should you  accept this one-time special order, and under what
circumstances? 
  What information do you need to make this decision? 
  suppose each probe costs $10 to produce, and 70% of this cost is due 
to one part, a fibre optic wire, that you also manufacture. 
  Should you continue to make this costly part, or should you buy it from 
an outside vendor, and under what circumstances? 
  What information do you need? 

