Cost Management


  Managing cost is especially important today because 
of: 
  shorter – 2 to 3 years – product life cycles, which require 
more accurate up-front projections about profitability of 
proposed investment, and leave less room for error in 
production planning and product costing; 
  increasing automation, which means that labor is no 
longer the only major overhead cost driver. 
  This requires more care in identifying, measuring and 
managing cost drivers. 

